      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://newsroom.ocfl.net/2021/04/from-boom-to-bust-to-boom-again-the-community-of-wedgefield-has-come-full-circle/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The community’s name comes from the wedge shape formed where State Roads 520 and 528 meet.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wedgefield%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "After Rocket City failed, Wedgefield grew into a quiet suburb where most homes sit on one‑acre or smaller lots.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3,
        8
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1",
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://wedgefieldcommunity.com/about"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Wedgefield Homeowners Association was born from the All‑State Development Corporation’s grand vision of a city larger than Orlando.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://wedgefieldcommunity.com/about"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "In the late 1960s, Banker's Life and Casualty Insurance inherited the abandoned Rocket City project, reshaping the area’s future.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        30
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://wedgefieldcommunity.com/about"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Wedgefield is part of the Orlando–Kissimmee Metropolitan Statistical Area, linking it to the larger Central Florida region.",
